  <Properties>
    <contentGrid>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f170b29c-338f-4ab8-a5c4-f72c90826f69",
      "key": "a688ba27-f5ef-4308-b45a-0f15c45b36cd",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c345e5ce-768f-47e0-968a-e7859dbe0b07",
      "key": "3372dfd3-6f3e-4f13-8353-e8f2325a7042",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "ca72c7ef-6198-4f35-a33c-4aaf18e7dafc",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "What It Does"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Displays child pages in a paginated card grid with navigation controls"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe Internal Links - Pagination feature displays child pages of the current page as a card grid with Bootstrap pagination controls. It shows a fixed number of pages per view (currently 3) with Prev/Next buttons and numbered page links.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is ideal for sections with many child pages where showing them all at once would overwhelm the page. The pagination controls include a fragment anchor so clicking a page number scrolls back to the pagination section rather than the top of the page.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "The page size is currently hardcoded at 3. This could be made configurable via a feature setting in future."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "5756c891-4f5d-49b0-88e2-670ad3ff8cbf",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How It Works"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Server-side pagination using query string parameters"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe view reads a \u003Ccode\u003Epage\u003C/code\u003E query parameter from the URL to determine which subset of child pages to display. It calculates the start index based on the page number and page size, then uses LINQ\u0027s \u003Ccode\u003ESkip()\u003C/code\u003E and \u003Ccode\u003ETake()\u003C/code\u003E to select the correct slice of pages.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPagination controls are rendered using Bootstrap\u0027s pagination component. The active page is highlighted, and Prev/Next links are disabled when at the boundaries. Each link includes a \u003Ccode\u003E#pagination\u003C/code\u003E fragment anchor to keep the user\u0027s scroll position near the pagination controls.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn BlockPreview mode (when \u003Ccode\u003EHttpContext\u003C/code\u003E is null), the view shows a simple preview message instead of the full pagination UI, since query parameters aren\u0027t available in the backoffice preview context.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "The current implementation doesn\u0027t handle multiple pagination blocks on the same page."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "2ede97b0-9580-41cc-a029-bf041790c209",
      "key": "b318ea81-7872-471c-a952-62f1788aa948",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c4b3a613-0d2c-4470-8d06-f7efea52d6e0",
      "key": "4da787cd-b49f-4a5d-a91b-217d6f1a7463",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyNavigationInPageItems",
          "culture": null,
